<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>Adverse Action Notice</title>
  <style>{% include "notice.css" %}</style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>Notice of Adverse Action</h1>
  <p class="meta">
  <dl class="meta">
    <dt>Creditor</dt><dd>{{ notice.creditor_id }}</dd>
    <dt>Date of action</dt><dd>{{ notice.date_of_action }}</dd>
    {% if notice.applicant_reference %}
    <dt>Applicant ref.</dt><dd>{{ notice.applicant_reference }}</dd>
    {% endif %}
    <dt>Decision system</dt><dd>{{ notice.agent_version }}</dd>
  </dl>
  </p>

  <h2>Action Taken</h2>
  <p class="action">{{ notice.action_statement }}</p>
  {% if notice.decision_rationale %}
  <p>{{ notice.decision_rationale }}</p>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>Principal Reasons for the Adverse Action</h2>
  <p>The principal reason(s) for our decision were:</p>
  <ul class="reasons">
    {% for reason in notice.principal_reasons %}
    <li>{{ reason.text }}{% if not reason.known %} <span class="gap">[reason code "{{ reason.code }}" not mapped to standard language]</span>{% endif %}</li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>

  <h2>Consumer Reporting Agency</h2>
  {% if notice.credit_reporting_agencies %}
  <p>
    Our decision was based in whole or in part on information obtained from the
    following consumer reporting agency/agencies. Under the Fair Credit
    Reporting Act you have the right to obtain a free copy of your report from
    the agency named below if you request it within 60 days, and to dispute the
    accuracy or completeness of any information in the report.
  </p>
  <ul>
    {% for cra in notice.credit_reporting_agencies %}
    <li>{{ cra.source_identifier }}</li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ul>
  {% else %}
  <p class="gap">[NOT CAPTURED] No consumer reporting agency was recorded for this decision.</p>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>Protected-Class Compliance Check</h2>
  {% if notice.protected_class_check %}
  <p>
    Automated check <em>{{ notice.protected_class_check.policy_name }}</em>
    (v{{ notice.protected_class_check.policy_version }}) result:
    <strong>{{ notice.protected_class_check.result }}</strong>.
  </p>
  {% else %}
  <p class="gap">[NOT CAPTURED] No protected-class compliance check was recorded.</p>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>Human Review</h2>
  {% if notice.human_review %}
  <p>
    Reviewed by role <strong>{{ notice.human_review.approver_role }}</strong>
    ({{ notice.human_review.approver_identity }}) —
    decision <strong>{{ notice.human_review.decision }}</strong>
    at {{ notice.human_review.decision_timestamp }}.
  </p>
  {% else %}
  <p class="gap">[NOT CAPTURED] No human review was recorded; this decision was made by an automated system.</p>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>Notice Delivery</h2>
  {% if notice.notice_delivery %}
  <p>
    This notice was dispatched via <em>{{ notice.notice_delivery.action_type }}</em>
    to {{ notice.notice_delivery.target_system }}
    (delivery {% if notice.notice_delivery.success %}confirmed{% else %}<span class="gap">not confirmed</span>{% endif %}{% if notice.notice_delivery.idempotency_key %}, ref {{ notice.notice_delivery.idempotency_key }}{% endif %}).
  </p>
  {% else %}
  <p class="gap">[NOT CAPTURED] No delivery of this notice has been recorded yet.</p>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>ECOA Notice</h2>
  <p class="legal">
    The federal Equal Credit Opportunity Act prohibits creditors from
    discriminating against credit applicants on the basis of race, color,
    religion, national origin, sex, marital status, age (provided the applicant
    has the capacity to enter into a binding contract); because all or part of
    the applicant's income derives from any public assistance program; or
    because the applicant has in good faith exercised any right under the
    Consumer Credit Protection Act. The federal agency that administers
    compliance with this law concerning this creditor is the Consumer Financial
    Protection Bureau, 1700 G Street NW, Washington, DC 20552.
  </p>

  {% if notice.credit_reporting_agencies %}
  <h2>FCRA Disclosure</h2>
  <p class="legal">
    In evaluating your application we obtained information from a consumer
    reporting agency. The reporting agency played no part in our decision and is
    unable to supply specific reasons why we have taken adverse action. You have
    a right under the Fair Credit Reporting Act to know the information contained
    in your credit file at the consumer reporting agency. You also have a right
    to a free copy of your report from the reporting agency if you request it no
    later than 60 days after you receive this notice, and to dispute with the
    reporting agency the accuracy or completeness of any information in your
    report.
  </p>
  {% endif %}

  {% if notice.model_governance %}
  <p class="footer">
    Model governance: {{ notice.model_governance.model_name }}{% if notice.model_governance.model_version %} ({{ notice.model_governance.model_version }}){% endif %},
    provider {{ notice.model_governance.provider }}{% if notice.model_governance.model_card_version %}, model card {{ notice.model_governance.model_card_version }}{% endif %}{% if notice.model_governance.prompt_template_version %}, prompt {{ notice.model_governance.prompt_template_id }}@{{ notice.model_governance.prompt_template_version }}{% endif %}.
  </p>
  {% endif %}

</body>
</html>
